 1917 Thursday 29 March Up at 6 a.m. soon readi for Corbi Train come along at 6.30 . Hayman Cassin join me on their way to Amien on leav for the day . Reach Edgehil C.C.S. walk along line to Merricourt , 2 mile . Catch French train to Amien . Arrive Corbi at 8.40 . a.m. Hunt for breakfast . No "mangez ? till 12 hour . At last get into a joint where am serv with steak 2 egg . Feel much refresh catch lorri for Daour . Arrive there enquir for cemetri , walk to it found Arnold Beatti 's grave . Place snowdrop upon it on behalf of his parent . Back to Corbi per lorri , visit church place of interest , catch anoth lorri which land me back near home at 4 p.m.
